# Accessibility Baseline

RHT-NAV is a public-facing government-adjacent policy site. It must meet
WCAG 2.2 AA and Section 508.

## Hard requirements

- Every interactive element is reachable by keyboard in logical order.
- Every `<img>` has a non-empty `alt` or `alt=""` for decorative images.
- Every `<button>` has an accessible name; icon-only buttons include
  `aria-label`.
- Color contrast meets WCAG AA (4.5:1 body, 3:1 large text).
- Leaflet maps include a textual fallback (the same data, rendered as a table
  or list elsewhere on the page).
- Framer Motion animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.
- Forms in the `/assumptions` workspace use `<label>` associations, not
  placeholder-only labels.

## Review hooks

- Agent #14 runs axe-core + Lighthouse on PR builds; failures block merge.
- The nightly Pre-Deploy Gatekeeper (#19) runs the a11y sweep against `main`.
